# Force LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# DataGuard ships committed sample artefacts (out/report.txt, the two
# attestations, and the sbom/ family). The compiler emits the SBOMs with
# LF on every OS, and the WASI backend writes the report/attestation with
# LF too, so the only way a regenerated tree could differ from what ships
# here is a checkout that rewrote committed LF to CRLF (core.autocrlf).
# Every tracked file is text (.capa, .json, .txt, .csv, .md, .toml, .sh,
# LICENSE, SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH); a blanket eol=lf is safe and keeps the
# reproducibility diff empty.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Reproducibility inputs, pinned LF for defence in depth.
sbom/SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH text eol=lf
generate.sh            text eol=lf
